kodkod.engine.fol2sat

Class Translation

  • java.lang.Object
    • kodkod.engine.fol2sat.Translation
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    Translation.Incremental, Translation.Whole

    public abstract class Translation
extends Object
    Stores the translation of a Kodkod problem to CNF. A problem consists of a formula, bounds and Options. A translation can be basic or incremental.
    Author:
    Emina Torlak
    Specfields:
    originalFormula: Formula // the original formula, as constructed by client
    originalBounds: Bounds // the original bounds, as constructed by client
    formula: Formula // optimization of this.originalFormula that was used for translation
    bounds: Bounds // optimization of this.originalBounds that was used for translation
    options: Options // the options object used to control translation
    vars: this.bounds.relations -> int // mapping from relations to variables that encode their contents
    solver: SATSolver // a SATSolver containing the CNF representation of the formula
    Invariants:
    solver.solve() iff SAT(formula, bounds, options)
    SAT(formula, bounds, options) iff SAT(originalFormula, originalBounds, options)
    this.originalBounds.relations in this.bounds.relations
    this.originalBounds.ints().equals(this.bounds.ints())
    all r: this.bounds.relations | some vars[r] => #vars[r] = this.bounds.upperBound(r).size() - this.bounds.lowerBound(r).size()
    all r: this.bounds.relations, i: vars[r] | min(vars[r]) <= i <= max(vars[r])
    vars[Relation] in this.solver.variables
    See Also:
    Translation.Whole, Translation.Incremental

      • cnf

        public abstract SATSolver cnf()
        Returns the SATSolver object containing the CNF encoding of this.formula. Satisfiability of the formula can be checked by calling SATSolver.solve(). Modification of the returned object may cause violation of Translation invariants.
        Returns:
        {s: SATSolver | SAT(s.variables, s.clauses) iff SAT(this.formula, this.bounds, this.options) }

      • interpret

        public final Instance interpret()
        If this.solver.solve() is true, returns an interpretation of the CNF solution as a mapping from Relations to sets of Tuples. The returned instance maps all relations in this.bounds and, therefore, all relations in this.originalBounds. The additional relations in this.bounds, if any, consist of generated skolem constants.

        The returned instance assigns the value instance.tuples(r) to each relation r in this.bounds.relations as follows: (1) instance.tuples(r) includes all tuples in this.bound.lowerBound(r), and (2) it includes the ith tuple from this.bounds.upperBound(r) - this.bounds.lowerBound(r) iff the model obtain from this.solver binds the ith variable in this.{@linkplain #primaryVariables(Relation) primaryVariables}(r) to true. In other words, if no primary variables were allocated to r, then the returned instance simply binds r to its lower bound. Note that in the case of a trivially satisfiable problem (this.formula, this.bounds, this.options), the returned instance is the smallest possible instance for that problem, consisting solely of the lower bounds specified by this.bounds.

        Returns:
        a new instance of the problem (this.formula, this.bounds, this.options), as described above
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - this.solver.solve() has not been called or the outcome of the last call was not true.

      • numPrimaryVariables

        public abstract int numPrimaryVariables()
        Returns the number of primary variables allocated during translation. Primary variables represent the tuples of relations in this.bounds that have different lower and upper bounds (i.e. some this.bounds.upperBound[r].tuples - this.bounds.lowerBound[r].tuples).
        Returns:
        #this.vars[Relation]

      • options

        public final Options options()
        Returns the translation options. Modification of the returned object may cause violation of Translation invariants.
        Returns:
        this.options

      • primaryVariables

        public abstract IntSet primaryVariables(Relation relation)
        Returns the set of primary variables that represent the tuples in the given relation. If no variables were allocated to the given relation, empty set is returned. This set contains exactly this.bounds.upperBound(r).size() - this.bounds.lowerBound(r).size() variable identifiers.
        Returns:
        this.vars[relation]

      • trivial

        public final boolean trivial()
        Returns true iff this translation is trivially true or trivially false. We consider a problem defined by this.formula and this.bounds to be trivially true or false if the Translator simplifies it to a BooleanConstant. The TRUE value is represented as a CNF with no variables and no clauses. The FALSE value is represented as a CNF with no variables and a single, empty clause. Note that in the case of a trivially satisfiable problem, the interpret() method returns the minimal trivial instance for that problem, which consists of the lower bounds specified by this.bounds.
        Returns:
        this.cnf.numberOfVariables() = 0
        See Also:
        interpret()
